.SH OUTPUT
The program outputs comprehensive computation results as JSON to stdout, including the braid, inversion data, degree, components count, and FK invariant coefficients. When the \-\-symbolic flag is used, human-readable polynomial expressions are shown instead.

.SS Single Computation Output
.nf
{
  "braid": [1, -2, -2, 3],
  "inversion_data": {
    "0": [1, -1, 1],
    "1": [1, 1, -1],
    "2": [-1, 1, 1]
  },
  "degree": 3,
  "components": 4,
  "fk": [
    [[-2, 1], [0, -1], [2, 1]]
  ]
}
.fi

.SS Batch Processing Output
.nf
{
  "trefoil": {
    "braid": [1, 1, 1],
    "inversion_data": {...},
    "degree": 2,
    "fk": {
      "q^-2": 1,
      "q^0": -1,
      "q^2": 1
    }
  },
  "figure_eight": {
    "braid": [1, -2, 1, -2],
    "inversion_data": {...},
    "degree": 3,
    "fk": {
      "q^-1": -1,
      "q^1": -1,
      "q^3": 1
    }
  }
}
.fi

.SS Symbolic Output
When using the \-\-symbolic flag, output appears as human-readable polynomial expressions in multiple formats:

.nf
# Default pretty format
fk simple "[1,1,1]" 2 --symbolic
q - q^3 + x^2*(-q^2 + q^6)

# LaTeX format
fk simple "[1,1,1]" 2 --format latex
$q - q^{3} + x^{2} \\left(-q^{2} + q^{6}\\right)$

# Mathematica format
fk simple "[1,1,1]" 2 --format mathematica
q - q^3 + x^2*(-q^2 + q^6)
.fi

Variables are chosen based on braid topology:
.IP \(bu 2
1 component: x
.IP \(bu 2
2 components: x, y
.IP \(bu 2
3+ components: a, b, c, d, ... (skipping 'q')

Requirements: SymPy >= 1.10 must be installed. Install with optional dependencies: \fBpip install fkcompute[symbolic]\fR.

.SS Output Fields
.TP
.B braid
The braid word used in the computation (may be modified during processing)
.TP
.B inversion_data
Dictionary mapping crossing indices to sign assignments from the inversion computation
.TP
.B degree
The degree parameter used for the invariant computation
.TP
.B components
Number of components/strands in the braid topology
.TP
.B fk
FK invariant coefficient matrix as nested lists of [power, coefficient] pairs
.TP
.B symbolic
Human-readable polynomial representation (only present when \-\-symbolic is used)
